<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN205">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>muṟṟiya tiruviṉ mūva rāyiṉum</l>
<l>peṭpiṉ ṟītal yāmvēṇ ṭalamē</l>
<l>viṟaṟciṉan taṇinta viraiparip puravi</l>
<l>yuṟuvar celcār vākic ceṟuvar</l>
<l>tāḷuḷan taputta vāṇmiku tāṉai</l>
<l>veḷvī vēlik kōṭaip poruna</l>
<l>ciṟiyavum periyavum puḻaikeṭa vilaṅkiya</l>
<l>māṉkaṇan tolaicciya kaṭuvicaik katanāy</l>
<l>nōṉcilai vēṭṭuva nōyilai yākuka</l>
<l>vārkali yāṇart tarīiya kālvīḻttuk</l>
<l>kaṭalvayiṟ kuḻīiya vaṇṇalaṅ koṇmū</l>
<l>nīriṉṟu peyarā vāṅkut tērō</l>
<l>ṭoḷiṟumarup pēntiya cemmaṟ</l>
<l>kaḷiṟiṉṟu peyarala paricilar kaṭumpē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Even though there are the Three of accomplished fortune, (1)</l>
<l>we don’t want [them] to give without desire. (2)</l>
<l>O fighter of mount Kōṭai with a white-flowered hedges, (6)</l>
<l>with an army abounding in swords who destroyed the laborious minds (5)</l>
<l>of the enemies, there being a refuge to go to for those who have (4)</l>
<l>fast-moving horses when victory has cooled the anger, (3)</l>
<l>o hunter with a sturdy bow, (9ab)</l>
<l>with fierce, speedy, angry dogs that destroyed a herd of deer, (8)</l>
<l>whose loopholes, small or big, were blocked, (7)</l>
<l>  may you be without pain. (9)</l>
<l>the relatives of gift-seekers won’t return with bull elephants, (14)</l>
<l>eminences who hold up [their] shining tusks, (13)</l>
<l>along with chariots, who keep moving like majestic clouds</l>
<l>without water that had come together on the side of the sea (11f.)</l>
<l>after they wind had made [them] descend in order to bring fertility with full bustle. (10)  </l>
</lg>
    </div>
